0000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufrogggystyle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Frogggystyle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/14/01 1:44:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.comedycentral.com/tv_shows/southpark//images/timmy1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RP too much to bear?</span><hr size=1> I was goofing around in GFay today to the tune of several whiners. The RP Nazis were out in force, making more of a disturbance than the so-called non-RP offenders. granted, this server is a 'roleplay prefered' server, it is first and foremost an alignment server. With this comes new challenges, not only in being able to understand others who play but also in who you can group with. The server puts people in a position to roleplay due to their character's alignment/class/diety/race, but it is not a requirement to play out your character. Not everyone roleplays the same as everyone else. <br>
<br>
What I know of RP is a bunch of people running around saying, &quot;Art doest thouest haveth stuffeth to giveth meith so I couldeth not be pooreth,&quot; or something like that. I saw some incredible RP'ers on today really playing out their chosen role, which was very impressive. But I think the server will suffer from the people who will persist in telling others how to play the game. Several people would just not shut up about people using WTS, SoW, WTB, etc. and it really ruined the gaming experience for me. I can not speak for others, but many people were firing back at them with comments that didn't help the situation at all. <br>
<br>
I came to the server to explore the new challenges that alignment restrictions impose on us. I thought it was a fascinating twist to the game. Some people are REALLY into RP while others are not into it all. So what is this server going to be? A bunch of intolerant players hellbent on saying 'hast thou doesth' or are we each going to just play the game in a fashion that allows us each to play our character the way we want? Technically speaking, EVERY server is an RP server. The game is an RPG and each person is permitted to RP if they choose to or not. This server, while it is prefered that you RP, is an alignment server that does not insist on a player RP'ing. Is the line to fine to distinguish what proper protocal is? I would hate to go back to my server as a result of a small group of people are going out of their way to make playing EQ a burden.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uyadensamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaden Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/14/01 1:52:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.rawbw.com/~jnewlin/yaden1.jpg height=85 width=85></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RP too much to bear?</span><hr size=1> *agrees*<br>
<br>
I came to this server looking for a challenge and a fresh start. I enjoy RPing casually but I have a feeling I will have little patience for the RP-nazis. <br>
<br>
Everyone, please remember to try to have fun and understand that not everyone is going spend 100% of their time adding -eth to everything they say. My character will have a background/story/attitude but I refuse to let my RPing hold me back from saying &quot;50m&quot; because I simply don't have all day to write out full sentences during a fight. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
