<br>
I think the problem with GFay is that it is just too full of people, period (prior to today, I had ventured into the zone each of the past 4 days - the zone crashed at least once every single time in there.).  As a result, it has the most friction, as you will see the full gamut of players.  You also have that /auction channel in your main hunting grounds, and is used for OOC: this is a major problem for this zone.<br>
<br>
Thankfully, the dwarven community has been great so far.  I have not seen much OOC content, and the groups I have been in thus far have tried very hard to roleplay: not just talking funny, but reacting as their character would act.<br>
<br>
Anyway, whereas I agree that excessive chastising of non-RPing behavior can be annoying, remember that excessive OOC commentary can be just as or more disruptive to those looking to get a bit more immersed in this game.  I just wish those that are not here to role play at all remember that there are many people here who are trying very hard to, and that they are impeding that effort with their OOC comments.<br>
<br>
/plead VI: reinstall /ooc - so that I and others may ignore it <p>-G<P><FONT size=-2>
<HR>
Ovor, Firiona Vie, Dwaven Rogue, N (8)<BR>
Ogbar, Veeshan, Dwarven Champion (52 - semi-retired)<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueliezeroferudin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/15/01 12:10:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RP too much to bear?</span><hr size=1> I agree, except on your characterization of the server as an Alignment Server.<br>
<br>
THIS IS NOT TEAMS.  Alignment is getting way to much press as a big issue.  It is a very small issue, that is just supposed to promote RP by making undesireable combinations difficult.<br>
<br>
Alignment should primarily be considered an IN CHARACTER guideline to how you ACT, not primarily an OOC rule to determine your groups.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, of course. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeffhead01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deffhead01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/15/01 6:22:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RP too much to bear?</span><hr size=1> This is NOT first and foremost an alignment server. It is a roleplaying server.<br>
Thus I can understand why many people are frustated with the rather large amount of players that come to the roleplaying prefered server, only to ignore its main purpose.<br>
<br>
And just because people feel differently, doesn't grant for you or anyone else to call them Nazi's. I have said it before and I'll gladly say it again. That expression pisses me off a good bit. Nazi's has nothing to do with this at all, and whoever thought it up, is @#%$ up in the head.<br>
They are just people that have a different opinion than you, so stop calling them Nazi's please.<br>
<br>
Lastly, I'd have to say that in my opinion, speaking in Shakespearian english (Thou, hast, ye, whatever) is not the defining element of roleplay. I do not see the NPCs speaking that way, so I can't see it being the norm in Norrath, so there is no need for players to do it. Do it if it suits your character, and don't if it feels wrong.<br>
 <p><b>Milton Finkelstein</b><br>
