for example, you'd expect a rogue to use less than the grammer of king James, an ogre to talk very simple, and a Dark Elf to be very rude. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueliezeroferudin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/15/01 7:33:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RP too much to bear?</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;  Why do you think RP Preferred is ahead of the server name? BECAUSE VERANT DEEMED IT AN ALIGNMENT SERVER. ITS JUST THAT RP IS NOW HEAVILY ACCEPTABLE.  &gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
Umm... Logic much?  How do you get Verant wanted an Alignment Server so they put RP preferred on it?<br>
<br>
READ the posts about it by Brad and others on the Verant Board.  Read the rules of the server.  It is a Roleplaying Server, but it is 'preferred' because if you choose not to Roleplay that isn't a violation of the Rules.<br>
