But they pretty clearly indicate that the POINT of the rules, Alignment included, is to encourage, foster, and aid in ROLEPLAY.  They didn't intend this as the 'difficult server,' or some sort of Gimped Team Server.<br>
<br>
Now, you ARE free to play the game as you desire.  Calling people who disagree with you Nazis however is low, demeaning, and uncalled for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uanklesdirtyfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ankles Dirtyfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mudslingin' Admin</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/15/01 7:56:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RP too much to bear?</span><hr size=1> I personally feel that referring to anyone as a &quot;Nazi&quot; is completely unacceptable in any circumstance, save those who follow true Nazi politics and ideology. <p><table width="400" height="125" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top" align="left" width="95" height="125"><img src="http://losingheidi.freeservers.com/face.gif"></td><td  valign="top" align="left" width="305"><font face="arial, system, courier new" size="-1" color="black"><b>Ankles Dirtyfoot &lt;<a href="http://www.geocities.com/starspunguild">Starspun</a>&gt;</b><br>
