<br>
Using Ankles' example is perfect.  There is nothing in the naming policy that says Ankles is an unacceptable name.  Yet she gets hounded by a name extremist who <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> personally</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> doesn't like her name.  This is where the extremists of any area don't have a leg to stand on.  They take the rules that are in place and twist them to their own ends.<br>
<br>
You are right that people do have a basis to petition names.  Many people aren't really aware of the full naming policy rules, even though they have been posted and circulated a thousand times.  I would not say that roleplaying advocates do not have a leg to stand on, however.  Extremists do not, but advocates do.  In addition to the naming policy, there are confinements to the use of the public channels and those limits are enforceable.  Abuse of those channels can hold the same punishments as abuse of any of Verant's policies.<br>
<br>
But what can they not enforce?  No one has to stay in character.  That is pretty obvious, seeing the addition of PREFERRED at the end of the ROLEPLAYING tag.  In fact, someone that hounds you over not staying in character can be warned for harrassment.  The roleplayers have to play within the policies as well.<br>
<br>
So I might offer to those that are so upset by the roleplaying extremists that you too have your rights to play on this server within the boundaries of Verant's policies.  If you see someone spamming the channels, petition them.  If you have someone harrassing you with condemnations for not roleplaying, petition them.  Why?  Because chances are if they are bugging you, they are also bugging several other people.<br>
<br>
I am a firm believer that a few rotten apples spoil a bunch, and that 90% of any environment consists of a cooperative and good minority.  Pull in the reigns on the other 10%  (griefers and extremists... take your pick of which side, doesn't matter), and the whole server benefits. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugreblaja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greblaja</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/15/01 11:29:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://grebslog.rigamer.com/everquest/ovor01.gif height=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RP too much to bear?</span><hr size=1> Use the term &quot;zealot&quot; - I have heard it used here before, and I think it applies in this case. <p>-G<P><FONT size=-2>
