<br>
I have to agree with Froggystyle that because of Verant's idea of how we should roleplay our characters (with the focus on deity, race, class and language restrictions) the server does seem to have more of a focus on alignment (Good vs. Evil) than roleplaying.  I'd hoped it would have more of a focus on free-form roleplaying, but I suspect Verant underestimated the number of people who wanted a server populated by roleplayers, and so they didn't want to scare the non-roleplayers off and end up with an empty server.<br>
<br>
I do not, however, think the Firiona Vie server will suffer from people suggesting that abbreviations like &quot;WTS, WTB, SoW&quot; and the like be avoided in open chat channels -- at least not any more than any server suffers from the green spam in East Commons or Greater Faymart, or the chatter and flames common to any large zone.  <br>
